# Agent OS environment template.
# Copy this file to .env (same directory) and fill in what you need:
#
#   1. At least ONE model provider key  -> chat + Coding Agent work locally.
#   2. TAVILY_API_KEY (optional)        -> enables @search web research.
#   3. Delivery connector tokens        -> enable GitHub push/PR, Vercel
#      deploys, Supabase migrations, and Stripe test payments.
#
# This file is the home for GLOBAL, account-level secrets. Per-project
# configuration (which GitHub repo, Vercel project id, Supabase project ref /
# db password, Stripe publishable key, ...) is set in the UI via the
# Connectors panel and lives in the gitignored credentials/ store. Secrets
# never appear in prompts, logs, run artifacts, memory, Git, or the UI.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Model providers (at least one required)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Agent OS supports six selectable model providers, each with a per-provider
# list of selectable models. A provider is available in the UI only if its key
# is set here; missing-key providers show as disabled. Claude is the preferred
# default when ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is set.

ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your-anthropic-key-here
OPENAI_API_KEY=
GOOGLE_API_KEY=
DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=
MOONSHOT_API_KEY=
ZHIPUAI_API_KEY=

# Accepted aliases (used only if the primary above is unset):
#   GEMINI_API_KEY  -> Gemini      (alias of GOOGLE_API_KEY)
#   KIMI_API_KEY    -> Kimi        (alias of MOONSHOT_API_KEY)
#   ZAI_API_KEY     -> GLM / Z.ai  (alias of ZHIPUAI_API_KEY)

# Optional — override the default model per provider without touching code.
# (Defaults are the latest API-available model per provider as of 2026-06.)
# AGENT_OS_CLAUDE_MODEL=claude-opus-4-8
# AGENT_OS_OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-5.5
# AGENT_OS_GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-3.5-flash
# AGENT_OS_DEEPSEEK_MODEL=deepseek-v4-flash
# AGENT_OS_KIMI_MODEL=kimi-k2.6
# AGENT_OS_GLM_MODEL=glm-5.2

# Optional — override the OpenAI-compatible chat endpoint (e.g. China-region
# hosts for Kimi / GLM, or a gateway / proxy).
# AGENT_OS_KIMI_BASE_URL=https://api.moonshot.cn/v1/chat/completions
# AGENT_OS_GLM_BASE_URL=https://open.bigmodel.cn/api/paas/v4/chat/completions
# AGENT_OS_OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1/chat/completions
# AGENT_OS_DEEPSEEK_BASE_URL=https://api.deepseek.com/chat/completions

# Optional — per-request LLM timeout in seconds (default 300).
# AGENT_OS_LLM_TIMEOUT=300

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2. Web research (optional) — powers the explicit @search / @research command
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Tavily API key for the bounded research channel. Without it, @search web
# search is unavailable (direct URL fetch still works keyless). Network access
# only ever happens on an explicit @search/@research turn.
# TAVILY_API_KEY=
# Alias: AGENT_OS_SEARCH_API_KEY

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 3. Delivery connectors (optional) — GitHub / Vercel / Supabase / Stripe
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Account-level tokens for the audited delivery pipeline. Every external
# action is a two-phase preview -> confirm contract; nothing pushes, deploys,
# migrates, or charges without an explicit confirmation in the UI.

# GitHub — push + PR creation. A classic PAT with `repo` scope, or a
# fine-grained token with Contents + Pull requests read/write. Injected only
# into git's environment at push time (GIT_ASKPASS), never argv/.git/config.
# The target repo per project is set in the UI (Git panel).
# GITHUB_TOKEN=
# Aliases: AGENT_OS_GITHUB_TOKEN, GH_TOKEN

# Vercel — deployments, redeploys, rollbacks, env-var pushes.
# Create at https://vercel.com/account/tokens; the per-project Vercel project
# id is set in the UI (Connectors panel).
# VERCEL_TOKEN=
# Alias: AGENT_OS_VERCEL_TOKEN

# Supabase — project status + CLI link/migrations (requires the Supabase CLI
# for migration contracts). Personal access token from
# https://supabase.com/dashboard/account/tokens; the per-project ref, URL,
# anon key, and database password are set in the UI (Connectors panel).
# SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN=
# Alias: AGENT_OS_SUPABASE_TOKEN

# Stripe — TEST-mode payments only (sk_test_...). Live keys are refused by
# default at the store boundary. Webhook signing secrets (whsec_...) are
# captured automatically when a webhook is registered through the contract
# flow and stored per project — never echoed back.
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=
# Alias: AGENT_OS_STRIPE_SECRET_KEY
